# CMS-BOOT-001 — ACF Pro Environment Verification

## Mission

Perform a complete verification of the WordPress CMS environment before implementing the CMS architecture.

Do NOT create any field groups yet.

Do NOT modify any existing content.

Do NOT register CPTs.

This mission is verification only.

---

## Verify ACF Pro

Confirm:

- ACF Pro is installed.
- Plugin is activated.
- License is active.
- Latest compatible version.
- No activation issues.

---

## Verify ACF Features

Confirm availability of:

- Options Pages
- Repeater Fields
- Flexible Content
- Clone Fields
- Relationship Fields
- Gallery Fields
- Group Fields
- Local JSON support

---

## Local JSON

Verify:

- Local JSON enabled.
- Save path.
- Load path.
- Repository compatibility.

Recommend whether Local JSON should become the canonical storage for Field Groups.

---

## Existing Content Audit

Inspect the current website.

Identify:

- Existing Pages
- Existing Posts
- Existing Custom Post Types
- Existing Taxonomies
- Existing Menus
- Existing Elementor Templates

Return an inventory only.

---

## Elementor Audit

Determine:

- Elementor version.
- Elementor Pro version.
- Existing Theme Builder templates.
- Dynamic Tag support.
- Compatibility with ACF.

---

## Theme Audit

Determine:

- Active Theme.
- Child Theme present?
- Theme supports template overrides?
- Existing custom PHP templates.

---

## Plugin Compatibility

Identify plugins that may interact with:

- ACF
- Elementor
- SEO
- Caching
- Forms

Highlight any conflicts.

---

## Performance Baseline

Record:

- PHP Version
- WordPress Version
- Memory Limit
- Upload Limit
- Active Cache
- Object Cache
- OPcache

---

## Risks

Identify anything that could affect CMS implementation.

---

## Recommendations

Return a Go / No-Go decision.

One of:

GREEN
Ready for CMS implementation

YELLOW
Minor issues

RED
Resolve blockers before proceeding

---

Do not implement anything.

Return only the readiness report.